Heat a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @British Beef Mince{240%grams} and @Sliced Mushrooms{120%grams} until the mince has browned and the mushrooms have softened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim the @Pak Choi{1}, then separate the leaves.

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{pinch}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the pak choi to the pan and stir-fry until just soft, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir in the @Ketjap Manis{25%grams}, @Soy Sauce{15%ml}, @Rice Vinegar{15%ml}, @Worcester Sauce{15%grams} and @Honey{15%grams}. Simmer until thickened slightly, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Add the @Udon Noodles{220%grams} to the pan. Toss to coat and simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add a splash of @water{a splash} if the sauce looks a little too thick.

Share your yaki style udon noodles between your #serving bowls{}. Sprinkle over the @Crispy Onions{1%sachet} to finish. Enjoy!